        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 2:25PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 225 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
De Queen, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
De Queen, Horatio, Lockesburg, Gillham, West Otis, West Line,
Geneva, Cerrogordo and Bellview.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
